<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Rocker Arm Assembly, Camshaft
        Assembly, Tappets, and Push Rods - Clean, Inspect, Measure, and Test - Camshaft Gear and Camshaft
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010503.3" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Camshaft Gear and Camshaft</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010503.3.1">
            <title>Clean Camshaft Gear and Camshaft</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a soft bristle brush and a suitable solvent to clean camshaft.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010503.3.2">
            <title>Inspect Camshaft Gear and Camshaft</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect camshaft. If any lobes are scuffed, scored, or cracked, replace camshaft.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010503.3.3">
            <title>Inspect and Measure Camshaft Gear and Camshaft</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect camshaft journal for wear.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure camshaft journal diameter to evaluate condition of camshaft journals lobes, with
                    an
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_X2100504.xml" xrefid="t210010504">Outside Micrometer</hotlnk>
                    . If any journals are worn beyond "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_S210010507.xml" xrefid="t210010501">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    ," replace camshaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure across dimensions A-D and B-C, with an
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_X2100504.xml" xrefid="t210010504">Outside Micrometer</hotlnk>
                    . Subtract B-C from A-D This is cam lobe lift. If any cam lobe wear exceeds "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_S210010507.xml" xrefid="t210010501">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    ," replace camshaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010520" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5221.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Measure camshaft lobe wear</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect camshaft thrust plate for wear, cracks, or distortion.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure thrust plate thickness with an
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_X2100504.xml" xrefid="t210010504">Outside Micrometer</hotlnk>
                    . If thrust plate wear exceeds "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_S210010507.xml" xrefid="t210010501">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    ," or is damaged or if there is excessive camshaft end play, replace thrust plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect camshaft drive gear for worn or damaged teeth. Replace as required.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect timing disk plate. Replace as required.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
